ref=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529698\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lrk1665702685508.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lrk1665702685508.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lrk1665702685508.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lrk1665702685508\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Substituting ProcScript Functions and Including Files in Static Server Pages\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">&lt;x-subst&gt;</span> tag to substitute some ProcScript functions (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formtitle</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$putmess</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$text</span>) or include files on a static server page.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"lrk1665702685508__context_w1181ab1b5b1_w1182ab1b5_w1183ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"lrk1665702685508__topic_d21749e1_d21750e1_d21751e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lrk1665702685508__p_d21752e1_d21753e1_d21754e1\">By default, the <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;head&gt;</code> element already contains some <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">&lt;x-subst&gt;</span> definitions, which you can copy and edit to add your own definitions. You can also use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">&lt;x-subst&gt;</span> functions inside the <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;body&gt;</code> tag.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lrk1665702685508__p_d21755e1_d21756e1_d21757e1\">To substitute a function or include a file:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrk1665702685508__li_d10646e1_d10647e1_d10648e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Design Layout worksheet, position the cursor in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;head&gt;</code> or the <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;body&gt;</code> tag.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lrk1665702685508__li_d10649e1_d10650e1_d10651e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lrk1665702685508__p_d21758e1_d21759e1_d21760e1\">Copy and paste one the examples already in the\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;head&gt;</code> and edit it to specify the desired function or file. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"abf1719476418454.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/abf1719476418454.html\" title=\"XHTML placeholder that is replaced by the value of the specified ProcScript function; one of $usp_formtitle, $putmess, or $text.\">&lt;x-subst type=\"function\"&gt;</a>and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kpx1719477633979.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kpx1719477633979.html\" title=\"XHTML placeholder that is replaced by the contents of a specified HTML or JavaScript file.\">&lt;x-subst type=\"inclFile\"&gt;</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bxj1719470647227.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>&lt;x-subst&gt;</a><p>The &lt;x-subst&gt; element is a placeholder for an HTML element that will be generated in the HTML for a static server page (USP). It determines the location, type, and attributes of the HTML element that will be substituted.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529698\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529698\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Substituting ProcScript Functions and Including Files in Static Server Pages Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Substituting ProcScript Functions and Including Files in Static Server Pages You can use the <x-subst> tag to substitute some ProcScript functions ( $formtitle , $putmess and $text ) or include files on a static server page. By default, the <head> element already contains some <x-subst> definitions, which you can copy and edit to add your own definitions. You can also use <x-subst> functions inside the <body> tag. To substitute a function or include a file: In the Design Layout worksheet, position the cursor in the <head> or the <body> tag. Copy and paste one the examples already in the <head> and edit it to specify the desired function or file. For more information, see <x-subst type=\"function\"> and <x-subst type=\"inclFile\"> . Related Links <x-subst> The <x-subst> element is a placeholder for an HTML element that will be generated in the HTML for a static server page (USP). It determines the location, type, and attributes of the HTML element that will be substituted. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}